LOKOJA – The Kogi Central Peoples Democratic Party, (PDP) Senatorial Candidate, Barr. Natasha Hadiza Akpoti-Uduaghan has charged the people of Kogi Central Senatorial District to ensure they register, transfer and collect their Permanent Voters Card, as the situation may demand. Natasha who received the PDP Certificate of Return on Monday in Lokoja alongside other Candidates of the party in the state further urged the people to turn out en-masse and vote for her and PDP teammates to ensure reformation from local communities to the State and the country at large. “There’s an awakening of the youths across the country in the pursuit of good governance through credible leadership and Kogi Central isn’t left behind this movement. “Joining my fellow candidates of our great party, the PDP to receive the Certificate of Return brings a new phase in our electoral process towards emerging victorious at the 2023 polls by God’s grace.